<div1 type="case">

<div2 type="caption">
                
<p>To the Honble The Judges of The Circuit Court of the District Court for the County of Washington.</p>
                
<p>The Petition of Ann Shorter for and on behalf of her Daughter Kitty and Kitty's Child William.</p>

</div2>

<div2 type="body">
                
<p>Humbly Sheweth,</p>
                
<p>That Your Petr's Child Kitty and Kitty's Child William, are detained in Slavery by Daniel Rapine; She therefore pray, that process may issue so, that the freedom of the said Kitty &amp; William may be asserted &amp; proven in this Court, And Your Petitioner will ever pray &amp;c.</p>
                
<p>H: Hiort for the Petitioner.</p>
                
<p>28 June 1808</p>
                
</div2>

<div2 type="back">

<pb xml:id="p002" facs="oscys.case.0003.001.002.jpg"/>

<p>19</p>

<p>Ann Shorter on behalf of Kitty &#38; William<lb/>
vs<lb/>
Rapine</p>

<p>Petn.</p>

<p>Mr Brent will please to issue sbpoena.<lb/>
H: Hiort.</p>

<p>Filed 1th July 1808.</p>

</div2>

</div1>
    
</body>
